	   <tr><td colspan=2>THE best pulling bow is the bow with the BEST range... damage should be second... wouldn't it be great to be able to hit a mob OUTSIDE of its casting range...<br><br>When looking for bows:<br>1) LONG Range: most important for pulling from far away, damage negligible<br>2) Short Range: want MOST damage because these will be dungeon bows<br>3) Dmg/Dly: Rangers best friend, can be used in combination with root/snare/DoTs to kite or whittle the enemies life down.<br>4) High Damage:&nbsp;&nbsp;good if you're not the puller but like to get a nice shot in as the Mob is Incoming<br>5) Low Delay:  Good to practice skill<br>&nbsp;<br>Darknyss Grimscale<br>53 Iksar ShadowKnight<br>24 Ranger, 23 Monk, 21 Enchanter</td></tr>
